CatDescriptText: Mrs. Pat Jackson, office worker, 108 Gareld Street, Natrona, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "How do you think Soviet Premier Khrushchev's visit to the United States affected relations between our country and Russia? Were you or were you not impressed by his visit to Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "I don't think that it has improved relations between the two countries.  They could have stayed in their own countries and negotiated.  I wasn't in the least impressed by the visit of Khrushchev to Pittsburgh.  It just didn't faze me."
